Resource Profile: PPL Packaged Product profile

Official URL: http://unicom-project.eu/fhir/StructureDefinition/PPLPackagedProductDefinition Version: 0.1.0
Draft as of 2024-07-10 Computable Name: PPLPackagedProductDefinition

Packaged Product

Usage:

  • Refer to this Resource Profile: PPL Packaged Product profile and PPL Marketing Authorisation profile
  • Examples for this Resource Profile: PackagedProductDefinition/Agen-5mg-Tablet-EE-PPD-1109887-A, PackagedProductDefinition/Agen-5mg-Tablet-EE-PPD-1109887-B, PackagedProductDefinition/CanifugCremolum-EE-PPD-1033692, PackagedProductDefinition/Cefuroxime-MIP-1500mg-EE-PPD-1529940 and PackagedProductDefinition/Cefuroxime-MIP-1500mg-EE-PPD-1529962

shelfLifeStorage 0..* ProductShelfLife Shelf Life and storage information

coding
system 0..1 uri Identity of the terminology system
Required Pattern: https://spor.ema.europa.eu/v1/lists/100000073343
period[x] 1..1 Duration, string The shelf life time period can be specified using a numerical value for the period of time and its unit of time measurement The unit of measurement shall be specified in accordance with ISO 11240 and the resulting terminology The symbol and the symbol identifier shall be used
containedItem 0..* BackboneElement An item (inner package or manufactured item) within the packaging
item 1..1 CodeableReference(PPL Packaged Product profile | PPL Manufactured Item profile) The actual item(s) of medication, as manufactured, or a device, or other medically related item (food, biologicals, raw materials, medical fluids, gases etc.), as contained in the package
amount 0..1 Quantity Number of the manufactured items (e.g. tablets) in this package layer or the amount of manufactured item (e.g. 20 g) in the unit of presentation defined in manufactured item definition
code 0..1 code Coded form of the unit
Binding: EMA SPOR All Units Combined (required)
